pr_title: [risk=no] Add labels to our local dev images

timeline.message: Add labels to our local dev images

timeline.bodyText: So is this pointing to an existing image somewhere? That's what most of the uses I see of this tag in the documentation are doing.
timeline.author: jaycarlton
timeline.diffHunk:
@@ -3,6 +3,7 @@ services:
   scripts:
     build:
       context: ./src/dev/server
+    image: allofustest/workbench-dev-api:local

replies.bodyText: No - per the PR description, we don't intend to push it anywhere, it's just a tag which will be applied to the image after being built. If an image with this tag already existed on your machine, it would use that instead.
replies.author: calbach
